<%- include('partials/header') %>

<div class="container py-5">
  <div class="text-center mb-4">
    <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold text-primary">🥗 About Nutrition Tracker</h1>
    <p class="lead">Your daily companion for smart eating and healthy living.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="row g-4">
    <div class="col-md-6">
      <div class="card shadow-sm border-0 h-100">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title text-success">🚀 Built With</h5>
          <p class="card-text">
            This application is developed using:
            <ul>
              <li>Node.js & Express.js (Backend)</li>
              <li>EJS (Templating Engine)</li>
              <li>MySQL (Database)</li>
              <li>Bootstrap 5 (Frontend UI)</li>
            </ul>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6">
      <div class="card shadow-sm border-0 h-100">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title text-success">💡 Features</h5>
          <p class="card-text">
            <ul>
              <li>Track calories and macros (Protein, Carbs, Fat)</li>
              <li>Log meals with flexible portion sizes</li>
              <li>See real-time BMI and calorie progress arcs</li>
              <li>Customize physical info and goals (cut/bulk/maintain)</li>
              <li>Weekly summaries and visual stats</li>
            </ul>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-12">
      <div class="card shadow-sm border-0">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title text-danger">👨‍💻 Who Made This?</h5>
          <p class="card-text">
            This project was built with by a passionate developer eager to combine tech with health & fitness. 
            The goal is to help students, professionals, and gym-goers better understand and manage their nutrition.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="text-center mt-5">
    <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg px-4">Go to Homepage</a>
  </div>
</div>

